******
[1] _Banana bunchy top virus_ - northern provinces
Date: Mon 2 Feb 2009
Source: Business Mirror [edited]
<http://businessmirror.com.ph/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5492:race-is-on-to-control-banana-disease-&catid=53:agri-commodities>


Race is on to control banana disease
------------------------------------
Agriculture experts in the region are exerting efforts to control the
spread of banana bunchy top disease in Cagayan Valley, a perennial
problem of banana farmers [in Isabela State]. Government agriculture
workers and researchers are doing regular rounds to rehabilitate
affected areas and protect other banana-producing places to improve
the productivity of farmers in the region, according to Dr Billy
Temanel, research and development chief of the Isabela State.

University agriculture records show that banana bunchy top disease
first occurred in Quirino province years ago but due to inaction, a
build-up of the plant virus inoculums ensued and the disease spread
throughout the region. At least 7175 hectares [17 730 acres] planted
with bananas in Quirino province have been infected with the disease
in the past years. The disease then occurred in other banana farms
each year. Efforts to contain the problem helped minimize its
occurrence, Temanel said.

The Cagayan Valley Agricultural Research and Development made a
series of probes to collect, measure, and identify all factors that
contribute to the growth and spread of the disease by identifying the
characteristics of the sites, the land use patterns, age and type of
plantations, farmer practices, adjacent vegetation and forest
patches, rainfall, and other climatic patterns, he added. Surveys
were done in Quirino, Nueva Vizcaya, and Isabela provinces.

[Byline: Rosenda B Alluad]

